1. Hello World

Write a Program that takes a word W as input and prints "Hello" followed by the given word.

Sample Input:
World
output:
Hello World

Solution:

import java.util.Scanner;

class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) { 
        // Write your code here
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        String word=sc.nextLine();
        System.out.println("Hello "+word);
        sc.close();
    }
}

2. Print the Input

Write a program that reads a single line of Input and print the given input.

Sample Input1:
Bat
output:
Bat

Sample Input2:
5
output:
5

Solution:

import java.util.Scanner;

class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) { 
        // Write your code here
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        String word=sc.nextLine();
        System.out.println(word);
        sc.close();
    }
}

3.Print the Input-2

For this problem you need to write code and read a single line of Input and print the line after message "Given input:"

Sample Input1:
Happy Coding
output:
Given input: Happy Coding

Sample Input2:
Tech Foundations
output:
Given input: Tech Foundations

Solution:

import java.util.Scanner;

class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) { 
        // Write your code here
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.print("Given input: ");
        String word=sc.nextLine();
        System.out.println(word);
        sc.close();
    }
}

4.Second Line

For this problem you need to write code and read a two lines of Input and print the second line of input.

Sample Input1:
Fundamentals
Python
output:
Pyhton

Sample Input2:
Tom
Jerry
output:
Jerry

Solution:

import java.util.Scanner;

class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) { 
        // Write your code here
        Scanner sc=new Scanner (System.in);
        String first=sc.nextLine();
        String second=sc.nextLine();
        System.out.println(second);
        sc.close();
    }
}

5. Print in Reverse Order

Write a program that reads a two lines of Input and print those two lines in the reverse order 
(Print the message in the second line of input before the first line of input)

Sample Input1:
Book
Pen
output:
Pen
Book

Sample Input2:
4
5
output:
5
4

Solution:

import java.util.Scanner;

class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) { 
        // Write your code here
        Scanner sc=new Scanner (System.in);
        String first=sc.nextLine();
        String second=sc.nextLine();
        System.out.println(second);
        System.out.println(first);
        sc.close();
    }
}

6.String Repetition

Write a Program to print the given input word N times in a single line seperated by space.

Sample Input1:
pen
2
output:
pen pen

Sample Input2:
Good Day
3
output:
Good Day Good Day Good Day

Solution:

import java.util.Scanner;

class Main
{
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        String first=sc.nextLine();
        String last=first+" ";
        int count=sc.nextInt();
        System.out.println((last).repeat(count));
    }
}

7. Reverse the Digits

For this problem you need to write code and read a single line of Input, which is a two digit integer, and print the two digit number by reversing the digits in it.

Sample Input1:
21
output:
